  "instructions": [
    "Mix the ground pork shoulder and lean pork with minced garlic, grated ginger, soy sauce, oyster sauce, fish sauce, salt, and pepper to form the filling.",
    "Place 1 teaspoon of filling onto each wonton wrapper, wet the edges with water, fold into triangles, and seal the seams.",
    "Heat a saucepan over medium heat and bring the water or broth to a gentle boil.",
    "Add the wontons to the boiling liquid and cook for 5 minutes, stirring gently to prevent sticking.",
    "Insert sliced peppadew peppers into the soup and reduce heat to a low simmer.",
    "Continue simmering for another 4 minutes, or until the wontons float and are cooked through.",
    "Drizzle sesame oil into the soup and stir.",
    "Remove the pot from heat, garnish with sliced scallion, and serve hot."
  ],
